43:32.231 --> 43:34.714
Look at English 19th century writing.

43:35.065 --> 43:40.390
where you have major writers and you have writers slightly less and slightly less and slightly less.

43:40.831 --> 43:49.199
So there's a rich texture, an undergrowth, and you're constantly discovering rather interesting and curious books.

43:50.200 --> 43:56.286
Not great books, but put together gives a richness to the literary soil.

43:57.947 --> 44:02.912
